## Covered Technologies

1. **Embedding-based semantic dispatch (chromatophore)** — US 64/010,742. System for
   translating AI agent emotion descriptors to LED animations and on-screen visual
   simulations via semantic embedding matching against a pre-computed capability library.
   Covers the emotion-to-animation mapping in `browser/js/led.js` and the semantic
   dispatch algorithm.

2. **Multi-model interpretive disagreement** — US 64/010,891. Method of processing input
   signals through multiple independent models and injecting all outputs into a large
   language model simultaneously, preserving inter-model disagreement as informational
   signal. Covers the dual-model transcription pipeline in `gpu-worker/handler.py`,
   self-similarity scoring, confidence tiering, and disagreement-modulated behavioral
   policy.

3. **Dynamic embedding-based rejection databases** — US 64/011,207. System for filtering
   unwanted signals using embedding-based semantic similarity against a dynamic rejection
   database collaboratively grown by users and autonomous agents. Covers the hallucination
   detection pipeline, speaker rejection via diarization, per-entry adaptive similarity
   radii, and the collaborative growth mechanism.

